[The 10th consecutive day with greater than 100 newly confirmed cases. Notices 511 and 512 at https://www.cdc.go.kr/board.es?mid=a30402000000&bid=0030 provide details on clusters as of 21 Aug 2020. These involve multiple clusters, some faith-based, some school-based, and other areas of work or communal gatherings. Faith-based congregations are the predominant groups with cases. Of the locally transmitted cases, 138 are in Seoul and 124 are in neighboring Gyeonggi province; 15 of 17 provinces have reported locally transmitted cases. Level 2 restrictions are being implemented, with no indoor dining and no in-person church services. The KCDC requested people cancel or postpone outings, social gatherings, events, or travel plans and stay home this weekend. - Mod.UBA]

